{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"EZR","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Ezra"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Ezra"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Ezra"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Ezra"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Ezra"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Proclamation of Cyrus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../2_chronicles/36.htm#22|>2 Chronicles 36:22–23</a>; <a href =|../isaiah/45.htm|>Isaiah 45:1–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, to fulfill the word of the LORD spoken through Jeremiah, the LORD stirred  the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia to send a proclamation throughout his kingdom and to put it in writing as follows: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"This is what Cyrus king of Persia says: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The LORD, the God of heaven, who has given me all the kingdoms of the earth, has appointed me to build a house for Him at Jerusalem  in Judah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Whoever among you belongs to His people, may his God be with him, and may he go to Jerusalem in Judah and build  the house of the LORD, the God of Israel; He is the God who is in Jerusalem. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And let every survivor, wherever   he lives,  be assisted by the men of that region with silver, gold, goods, and livestock, along with a freewill offering for the house of God  in Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"So the family heads of Judah and Benjamin, along with the priests and Levites— everyone whose spirit God  had stirred— prepared to go up and rebuild  the house of the LORD  in Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And all their neighbors supported them with articles of silver and gold, with goods and livestock, and with valuables, in addition to all their freewill offerings. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Cyrus Restores the Holy Vessels"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"King Cyrus also brought out  the articles belonging to the house of the LORD that Nebuchadnezzar had carried away from Jerusalem and placed in the temple of his gods. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Cyrus king of Persia had them brought out by the hand of Mithredath the treasurer, who counted them out to Sheshbazzar the prince of Judah. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the leader of the exiles returning to Judah"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"This was the inventory: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["30 gold dishes, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>basins</i>; twice in this verse"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["1,000  silver dishes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["29  silver utensils, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"30 gold bowls, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["410   matching silver bowls, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and 1,000 other articles. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"In all, there were 5,400    gold and silver articles. Sheshbazzar brought all these along when the exiles went up from Babylon to Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The List of Returning Exiles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../nehemiah/7.htm#4|>Nehemiah 7:4–69</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now these are the people of the province who came up from the captivity of the exiles  carried away to Babylon by Nebuchadnezzar its king . They returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his own town, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," accompanied by Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum, and Baanah. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Parallel text at Nehemiah 7:7 <i>accompanied by Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, and Baanah</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["This is the count of the men  of Israel: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"the descendants of Parosh, 2,172   ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"the descendants of Shephatiah, 372   ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"the descendants of Arah, 775   ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"the descendants  of Pahath-moab through the line of Jeshua and Joab), 2,812    ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"the descendants of Elam, 1,254   ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"the descendants of Zattu, 945   ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"the de